Explain the topic: <Alternative Constructor>

Follow this exact note-making structure:

1. One-line definition  
- Explain in very simple language (1–2 lines only)

2. Why this topic exists (purpose)  
- What problem does it solve?
- Why do we need it?

3. Where it is used (Data Analyst context)  
- Real-world usage related to data analysis

4. Core concepts / keywords  
- List only important keywords (no explanations, no paragraphs)

5. Syntax  
- Show only the basic and most common syntax

6. Simple example  
- Very basic example to understand the concept
- No complex logic

7. Data Analyst example  
- Practical example related to data, CSV, Pandas, analysis, or automation

8. Common mistakes / confusions  
- Mistakes beginners usually make

9. Interview questions  
- 2–3 commonly asked interview questions

10. One-line summary  
- Short memory-friendly conclusion

Rules:
- Avoid long paragraphs
- Keep language simple
- No unnecessary theory
- Focus on clarity, revision, and interviews
 